702917f-a.title: Brooklyn: 92nd Street (East) - Skidmore Lane
702917f-a.text:
East 92nd Street, east side, north of Skidmore Lane, showing in the Nright foreground, (N .E. corner), is the Skidmore's store (Nos. 1919-1927 East 92nd Street) and post office; from 1860-1873. In the background, may be seen the steeple of St. Matthews German Lutheran Church, which was erected in
1879.
March 1925.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

702918f-a.title: Brooklyn: 92nd Street (East) - Skidmore Lane
702918f-a.text:
East 92nd Street, east side, south from Skidmore Lane, showing at the
right, the Grace Methodist Church.
June 1928.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collectdon.
